iter50 (2026-05-26): MAJOR rs-learn fix landed. (1) Root-caused why iter33-wired cores were unusable: each learn dispatch makes a FRESH LearnSession, so router/instant/attention in-RAM state evaporated between dispatches (only the graph core persisted, being KV-backed). Wired the EXISTING but uncalled save_*/load_* persist functions into dispatch.rs handlers (save-after-mutate + lazy-load-on-None) for router/instant/attention/deep-fisher; added graph/attention_persist.rs + nudge_relation verb. rs-learn 3872bd9. (2) Then validating on live 0.1.583 surfaced a deeper bug: wasm_host::kv_put had the host return-code convention INVERTED (host returns 1=success/0=fail, rs-learn read rc==0 as Ok). Graph+pipeline masked it via let _ =; error-propagating callers (the new persist fns AND wasm_learn.rs file-vec memorize path) failed on writes that actually succeeded. Fixed to rc!=0 => Ok (rs-learn 65fdad9). Both pushed, cascaded to plugkit 0.1.584 (in-flight). Graph cross-dispatch round-trip (insert_edge then query_at separate dispatches) re-validated count:1 on 0.1.583. Router/instant round-trips block on 0.1.584 landing. Detailed the persistence model in paper.html s40 (browser-witnessed). Pruned 2 stale memories (rlib-out-of-reach + cores-unbridged, both falsified). LESSON: when adding KV-persisting code to rs-learn, the host_kv_put convention is 1=success; match the graph core pattern.